cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC

This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on autonomous agents performing manipulation tasks. Computer Vision (cs.CV) is also likely as the approach involves detecting and extracting grasp affordances from visual input. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible sub-category as the paper uses Markov Logic Networks to build a knowledge base graph representation. Machine Learning (cs.LG) is also a possibility as the paper discusses learning prototypical grasping patches from examples. Finally, Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) is a less likely but still possible sub-category as the paper evaluates the success of the grasping task on a robotic platform.
